Defendant Kenbrell Martrell Hill in court with attorney Thomas J. Kasen.  Defendant Kenbrell Martrell Hill in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 7 years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 3 years.  Defendant shall serve 4 years  on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is  eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but not for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, if not previously provided.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay restitution to Terri H., in the stipulated amount of $1,700.00, joint and several with co-actor in 14CF1783, plus the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements, all to be taken by the Department of Corrections from prison funds not to exceed 25%. Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with the victims Teri H., Dejevon C., Kevin B. or D.W.H. (d/o/b 11-20-07);
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - No contact with co-actor Jovanta Coretz White;
 - Pay any balances remaining of the restitution, costs, surcharges and disbursements as ordered.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

